Introduction

Lee Jin Hyuk (formerly known as Wei) is a South Korean singer, rapper, and actor under TOP Media. He made his official debut in 2015 as a member of the boy group UP10TION.

In 2019, Jinhyuk, along with fellow member Wooshin, participated in Mnet's boy group survival show Produce X 101. He was eliminated in the finale after finishing in 12th place. Following this, TOP Media announced that both of them will be focusing on solo activities and will not be participating in group promotions indefinitely.

Jinhyuk made his solo debut on November 4, 2019, with the mini album S.O.L. The next year, he made his acting debut through the drama "Find Me in Your Memory."

On November 27, 2014, it was reported that he is exempt from mandatory military enlistment due to a congenital heart condition. Because of this condition, Lee Jin-hyuk is unable to fulfill his military service duties. It is reported that he continues to visit the hospital regularly to manage his health condition.
